meta.job_title: Tenure-Track Assistant Professor, Counseling and Counseling Psychology Program

duties_responsibilities.duty: Teach graduate courses in Counseling and Counseling Psychology
Participate and mentor student participation in professional counseling and psychology associations
Maintain an active research program that aligns with the land grant mission and national impact
Provide service at various levels within professional counseling and psychology associations
Provide clinical supervision for Counseling and Counseling Psychology students
Perform other duties as assigned by the School Head

education_certification.credential: Doctoral degree in Counselor Education and Supervision (CACREP Accredited) or Counseling Psychology (APA Accredited)
